This article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama in response to the tragedy that occurred in Tucson, Arizona on January 8, 2011. The proclamation orders that the flag of the United States be flown at half-staff at the White House, public buildings, military posts, naval stations, and naval vessels of the Federal Government in the District of Columbia and throughout the United States and its Territories and possessions until sunset on January 14, 2011. The flag is also to be flown at half-staff at all United States embassies, legations, consular offices, and other facilities abroad, including military facilities and naval vessels and stations.